channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Dems in Shaky Seats Plan to Avoid Chicago Convention and Harris/Walz Coronation
FLASHBACK: Walz backed 'alternatives to policing' package at height of defund movement
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz pushed a legislative package that included "alternatives to policing" in the days after the death of George Floyd in 2020.

item.title: Illegal Immigration Focus Shifts to Northern Border
item.description: Lawmakers are shifting some of their focus on border security to the north, aiming to control the growing migration problems along the U.S.-Canada border.

item.title: Megyn Kelly Exposes the Fantasy Repackaging of Kamala With New Word They're Using to Rebrand Her
Walz's honeymoon with China gets fresh scrutiny as Harris camp blasts 'lying' critics
item.description: Tim Walz, Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate, is facing scrutiny over previous visits and alleged pro-China comments he has made. The Harris campaign disputes this.

item.title: FEC Won't Mandate Political Ad AI Use Disclosure
item.description: The Federal Election Commission will not require political advertisers to disclose their use of artificial intelligence in broadcast television and radio ads this year, Republican chair Sean Cooksey told Axios.

item.title: WATCH: British Police Commissioner Threatens to Jail People Over Social Media Posts
Walz accusations of 'stolen valor' prompt battle between House veterans
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz's military record is at the center of the latest partisan showdown in the House of Representatives.

item.title: Rep. Stauber to Newsmax: Harris Vetting Team 'Probably Fired by Now'
item.description: Rep. Pete Stauber, R-Minn., told Newsmax on Friday that Vice President Kamala Harris' vetting team has "probably been fired by now" after allegations of stolen valor surfaced against newly-picked running mate Tim Walz.

item.title: Louisiana Judge Faces Punishment for Slowing Down Child Pornography, Domestic Violence Investigations
Republicans ask Supreme Court to allow Arizona proof of citizenship law to be enforced
item.description: The Republican Party is urging the Supreme Court to allow Arizona to implement a voting law that would require proof of citizenship before individuals are allowed to vote.

item.title: Feds: Dems' Convention Faces Threat of 'Retaliatory' Attack
item.description: Federal security officials have been put on alert for the potential of retaliatory attacks against Democrats at the party's upcoming convention in Chicago after the attempted assassination of former President Donald Trump, according to a threat assessment.

item.title: After Rash of Home Invasions, Encino Residents Arm Themselves; LAPD Captain Says They're 'Overreacting'
Biden hunkers down at Delaware beach house after only public event of the week
item.description: President Biden has retreated to his home in Rehoboth Beach in Delaware after holding only one public event this week at the White House.

item.title: Black Americans Will Reject Kamala Harris, Especially Men
